&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Technician - Production&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an experienced Pharmacy Technician to join our team at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital in King&#39;s Lynn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Lead Technician for production you would join our aseptic services team, assisting with the co-ordination of the aseptic service, undertaking the day-to-day supervision of activities and training staff. You will manage all technical staff working in the pharmacy production unit and manage the processes required to ensure the accurate and timely provision of all medication from the unit to individual patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from enthusiastic, motivated individuals with a working knowledge of aseptic processes and hospital services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to hold a BTEC, City &amp; Guilds or NVQ 3 or an equivalent Pharmacy Technician’s qualification and pharmacy experience as a registered Pharmacy Technician.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this role fits your profile, we would love you to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note due to high volume of applications for some posts, this post may close before the displayed closing date. We recommend that you apply for this role as soon as possible.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, or to arrange an informal visit, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Karen Sunshine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01553 613783&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: karen.sunshine@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
